Gotta get these legs ready for the season! Crazy how fast it came but time to catch up! 

If you know my history in snowboarding I have a great list of accomplishments, but also an even longer list of injuries. 

But every time I was injured the doctor would tell me how long I would have to be off a snowboard. Whatever the time frame was that they told me I would respect what they had to say but I would always rest for the time needed until I was able to get back to PT or the gym! 

I popped both ankles last season, one OPENING day, then the next ankle 3 months after, while having to film a part. THE MADNESS WAS REAL!!!

Whatever your going through don’t quit there is better for you right around the corner!!! God doesn’t give us more than we can’t bare!

SKIP EXCUSES! 

I woke up this morning tired and wanting to give myself the excuse of “ its Saturday you worked hard, just sleep in and get to it in a bit!” Something snapped for me to get up! 

So I got up made a protein shake and headed to the gym not realizing they open on Saturday at 7:30am, and I was there at 6:30am 😱😄 (should have checked the hours lol)

So I start think, we’ll I’m not going home I need to still get a workout where should I go? @andyfrisella will tell you in #75HARD you can workout on a hill, outside your front door, you don’t need a gym to get a workout. So I can to Bear Mountain to run and do some drills instead of sitting in bed.

What a ride with @djvip510 

We went 46 miles on the dirt bikes and man was it a great ride!

Quick update!
I’m able to sit on my ankles and sit on them for a while now! Ankles play a big roll in snowboarding! 

It’s important to not only keep your ankles great but your whole body aswell! And recovering from injuries take twice the time to recover and get strong! 

But with the right movement and workouts and recovery plan  you can build your body back in insane time!!!! 

M in d you I tore both ankles last season and already back and ready to go for opening day!!! 

Appreciate all my sponsors that know injuries are part of the game and believe in my abilities!!!
